<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7218> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7218" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Shackleton Bailey has shown that these two entries (MRR 2.580, Index) describe the career of one person, a Iunius Brutus Damasippus who was adopted by a P. Licinius Crassus. Delete the cognomen Dives. See Shackleton Bailey, Studies 46-47; AJAH 1, 1976, 162-163. On his coinage when he was legatus pro praetore in Africa in 47-46 (MRR 2.301, and Index, 580), see now Crawford, RRC 1.472, no. 460, inscribed P. CRASSVS IVN. LEG. PROPR. He may have been a praetor in 51 (Cic. Att. 5.3.2: Edictum P. Licini; cf. Willems, Senat 1.515, no. 303).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6894> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6894" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A senator, who was with Juba in Africa in 49 (Caes. BC 2.44) and was killed there in 46 (Bell. Afr. 96). On the name, see CIL 1(2).2.1344." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5841> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5841" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus pro praetore under Metellus Scipio and Cato in Africa (Grueber, CRRBM 2.571f.; Plut. Cat. Min. 70.3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5590> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5590" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably a Pompeian officer (Legate?) in Caria in 49-48 (BCH 14 [1891] 232; and on his title, see 46, Legates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5275> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5275" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cicero dissuaded him from joining Hirrus in proposing a dictatorship for Pompey (Cic. QF 3.8.4; see above, Coelius Vinicianus)." .
